div1.p: In the District Court of the Territory of Washington, holding terms at Seattle for the Countries of Kingand Kitsap: ---
United States of America vs: Leonard Martin} ORDER.

On reading and filing the petition of the said Leonard Martin duly signed and verified by him and in his behalf by his Attorney atlaw, James H. Lewis, whereby it appears that he is illegally imprisoned and restrained of his liberty by John H. Mc.Graw sheriff of the County of King in the Territory of Washington at the County-Jail in said County in the City of Seattle, and stating wherein the illegallity consists, form which it appears to me that a writ of habeas Corpus ought to issue;--

IT IS ORDERED - that a writ of Habeas Corpus issue out of and under the seal of the said District Court of the said Territory of Washington in and for the County of King, directed to the said Jr H. Mc. graw Sheriff as aforesaid commanding him to have the baxxbody of the said Leonard Martin before me in the Court room of the said District Court at Seattle on the 21st, day of May 1885, at hald past nine Oclock in the forenoon of that day, to do, and receive what sahall then and there be considered concerning the said Leonard Martin together with the time anf cause of his detention, and that he have then and there the said writ
4432 FILED May 20, 1885 James Seavey, Clerk By James P Laudlow Deputy Clerk,
